You can implement a kind of post-check monitor:
```
public class Monitor implements ApplicationContextAware, InitializingBean {
    private ApplicationContext ctx;

    @Override
    public void setApplicationContext(ApplicationContext ctx) throws BeansException {
        this.ctx = ctx;
    }

    @Override
    public void afterPropertiesSet() throws Exception {
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(ctx.getBeanDefinitionNames()));
        // run any checks you need
    }
}
```

With `org.springframework.beans.factory.config.BeanFactoryPostProcessor` you can gain even more details and controls before beans actual initialisation.

